The paper deals with the problem of vehicle re-identification using domain adaptation techniques. Therefore, it is likely to belong to the Computer Vision (cs.CV) category. The paper proposes a novel framework that involves the use of an image-to-image translation network and an attention-based feature learning model, which are both related to machine learning (cs.LG) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI). The proposed framework is evaluated on two datasets, which are related to multimedia (cs.MM) and information retrieval (cs.IR).
